Interface SearchNode<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - Object held within this node
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsearchNode

    public interface SearchNode<E>
    SearchNode is a node used when completing searches (e.g. BFS, A* Search). Each node can be viewed as a state space.

    A single object is contained within each node.
    Author:
    Hayden Charles Smith, z3418003
    Last modified: 19th May 2013
